 Peddie - The Peddie SAPS Detective Unit is looking for relatives or next-of-kin following the discovery of a body of a man, estimated to be about 40-years-old. According to police spokesperson, Captain Khaya Tonjeni, the body was found buried next to the road at Gcinisa village, Peddie  (near Mambalwini and Mqwashwini). "This discovery happened after a community member saw a hand of a person showing from under the soil on the gravel road drainage," he described. "The community member immediately reported the frightening discovery to the police, yesterday, 07 December 2019. "The body had visible wounds on the upper body. "He was dressed in a black leather jacket and maroon pants.  He had a brown Strachan hat and white flip flops on his feet. His hairstyle is long dreadlocks." Capt Tonjeni said that on his right hand, three of his fingers had rings on. "Police are looking for family, friends, relatives or next of kin of the deceased. Any family missing a man fitting this description are requested to please contact WO Mkululi Manisi on 082 3019 713 or Peddie Detectives on 040 673 3311 for identification," he added. "All correspondence will be treated with strictest confidence." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 